  "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nAt slot 0 of epoch, computeNewStateRoot somehow has a very big `hashTreeRoot()` time\r\n\r\n<img width=\"659\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-12-15 at 13 47 46\" src=\"https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/assets/10568965/deded4d3-a5ac-4930-b660-4e369cb4140d\">\r\n\r\n[produce_block_holesky.cpuprofile.zip](https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/files/13682039/produce_block_holesky.cpuprofile.zip)\r\n\r\nThis happens a long time ago since https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/issues/5793#issuecomment-1647133160\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nFast `hashTreeRoot()` call in `computeNewStateRoot()` as the pre state there should cache a lot of hash objects already\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n_No response_\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_\n\n### Operating system\n\nLinux\n\n### Lodestar version or commit hash\n\nv1.12.1",
